  <name>Gerbil</name>
  <summary>Local LLMs, fully under your control</summary>
  <description>
    <p>
      Gerbil is a desktop app for running large language models and image generation locally.
      It handles backend downloads, GPU detection, and process management so you can get started
      without touching the terminal.
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>Automatic backend download and updates</li>
      <li>GPU auto-detection for CUDA, ROCm, Vulkan and Metal</li>
      <li>Image generation presets for Flux, Chroma and others</li>
      <li>HuggingFace model search and download</li>
      <li>SillyTavern and OpenWebUI as optional frontends</li>
      <li>Everything runs locally: no data sent to external servers</li>
    </ul>
  </description>

  <launchable type="desktop-id">dev.lonecloud.gerbil.desktop</launchable>
